<item>
            <title>[HIVE-6684] Beeline does not accept comments that are preceded by spaces</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-6684</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Beeline throws an error if single-line comments are indented with spaces. This works in the embedded Hive CLI.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SELECT&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;#8211; this is the field we want&lt;br/&gt;
   field&lt;br/&gt;
FROM&lt;br/&gt;
   table;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Error: Error while processing statement: FAILED: ParseException line 1:71 cannot recognize input near &apos;&amp;lt;EOF&amp;gt;&apos; &apos;&amp;lt;EOF&amp;gt;&apos; &apos;&amp;lt;EOF&amp;gt;&apos; in select clause (state=42000,code=40000)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
