                            <comment id="13938156" author="rem120" created="Mon, 17 Mar 2014 18:19:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The description doesn&apos;t render properly on my browser - the 2nd, 3rd and 5th lines of the example start with three spaces.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988304" author="rem120" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 21:48:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added patch with unit test - please review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988547" author="xuefuz" created="Sat, 3 May 2014 02:52:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good. Minor nit though, is that in the line&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; line.trim().startsWith(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;#&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) || line.trim().startsWith(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;--&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;line.trim() may be called twice, which is unnecessary. Better if just to trim once.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
